[I] GNOME Bluetooth subsystem

[T] The core of GNOME Bluetooth is two packages: gnome-bluetooth, which provides
[T] desktop level support for Bluetooth devices, and libbtctl, which provides a
[T] GLib style library of application support for accessing Bluetooth under Linux.

[U] http://usefulinc.com/software/gnome-bluetooth

